# __REPO_NAME__ Runbook

## Purpose

This runbook captures the current operator procedure for `__WORKFLOW_NAME__`.

## Before a run

- confirm `doctor.py` and `preflight.py` are clean enough to start
- confirm `AGENTS.md` reflects the current repo reality
- confirm repo guidance and issue templates describe secret and sensitive-data handling
- confirm workflow branch assertions and required-path anchors still match the repo
- confirm campaign metadata, routing labels, and closeout instructions still match the intended run
- confirm only trusted operators can create or edit issues matching the workflow routing label
- confirm the worker command allowlists only the environment variables this run needs
- confirm the first execution wave fills worker slots without file overlap

## During a run

- watch `In Review`, blockers, retries, and no-progress suppressions
- integrate validated worker output quickly
- redact any secret or sensitive data that leaks into issue bodies, comments, or logs
- record repeated issues or useful tactics in `LEARNINGS.md`

## After a run

- update this runbook with any operator step that should repeat next time
- promote stable learnings into `AGENTS.md`, the workflow, or the issue template
- clear or revise suppressions only after the ticket or workflow has materially changed
- remove stale notes that no longer reflect reality

## Repo-specific checks

- add branch rules, release constraints, dashboards, or review cadence here

## Known sharp edges

- clone or bootstrap failures that produce the wrong workspace shape
- no-progress runs that should be requeued instead of left burning tokens
- sensitive data leaking into Linear or `.orchestration/` artifacts
